             Major("Political Science",arrayListOf(Course("Introduction to Law","LAW 101","This course aims to provide the students with the main ideas and principles of law, such as: The definition of law, the elements of the legal rules, its kinds and sources of law . ","1","http://kretschmer.cc/pdf/introduction_1.pdf","NONE") ,
                 Course("Commercial Law","LAW 201","This course cover definition of the commercial law, its theories, bases and sources which constitute the main study in this course. It includes also a number of issues: The commercial contract, principles and kinds of banking operations, and bankruptcy.","2","https://www.wto.org/english/thewto_e/acc_e/vnm_e/wtaccvnm43_leg_11.pdf","LAW 101"),
                 Course("Public International Law","Law 303","The aim of this course is to introduce the public international law to political science students. It covers a number of topics: Definition of the international law, its source; the state from a legal viewpoint; sovereignty, equality of states and recognition.","3","https://prawo.uni.wroc.pl/sites/default/files/students-resources/introduction%20to%20public%20international%20law.pdf","LAW 101,POL 201"),
                 Course("Conflicts & Arbitration","LAW 401","This course explains, first, the public theory of peaceful arrangements for international conflicts. The second section focuses on the difference between political and the legal conflict.","4","https://icsid.worldbank.org/sites/default/files/Background_Papers_Issue_Conflict_Final_2.26.2021.pdf","LAW 303"),
                 Course("Political Science (1)","POL 101","This course deals with a number of topics, such as: The definition of political science and its relation with other social sciences. Theory of the state is dealt with in detail, to some extent; the definition of state and its essential elements, origin as well as forms of the state (united and federal).","1","https://www.hse.ru/data/2018/01/26/1162911138/program-1828008040-waENlZ082g.pdf","NONE"),
                 Course("Introduction to Political Science (2)","POL 201","This course focuses on the comparative political systems and their classifications. Pressure groups are discussed in some detail. To be added is the field of international relations: Meaning of the concept. main factors in international relations, elements of the national power of the state, international system old and new. It casts also light on the history of political thought.","2","https://www.hse.ru/data/2018/01/26/1162911138/program-1828008040-waENlZ082g.pdf","POL 101"),
                 Course("History of Political Thought","POL 301","It is one of the core courses in this field. It trace Western Political thought during successive ages: Ancient Greek, Roman, Christian, Middle Ages, modern as well as the contemporary times.","3","https://scholarcommons.sc.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?referer=&httpsredir=1&article=1018&context=poli_facpub","POL 201"),
                 Course("Theory of Comparative Political Systems","POL 302","This course aims to provide the students with the main ideas in such field. Basic concepts are to be discussed in depth: System, comparative analysis, elements of a political system, and main institutions, formal and informal.","3","https://www.shivajicollege.ac.in/sPanel/uploads/econtent/64f62e627be9f3fa4849dbf539388fe0.pdf","POL 201"),
                 Course("Theory of International Relations","POL 303","Definition of I.R is the starting point in this course. The essential elements of national power of the state are discussed. Classification of states into small, medium, big and super are explained. This course also discusses the representatives in the foreign scene: States, international organizations, multi-national corporations, pressure groups and non- governmental organizations.","3","http://www.e-ir.info/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/International-Relations-Theory-E-IR.pdf","POL 201"),
                 Course("International Organizations","POL 304","This course aims to study the international organizations in general Therefore, it deals with a number of points such as international organization and its development. ","3","https://www.asil.org/sites/default/files/ERG_IO.pdf","POL 201"),
                 Course("International Relations in the 20th Cent","POL 305","This course deals with the diplomatic history of the world. It starts with a hint to international developments in the 17th, 19th centuries. Then it concentrates, in details, on the 20th century, particularly the two major world wars; their causes and effects.","3","https://www.colaisteeanna.ie/wp-content/uploads/2011/01/History-Revision-International-Relations-in-the-20th-century.pdf","POL 201"),
                 Course("Diplomatic and Consular Systems","POL 306","This course explains the meaning and history of diplomacy as a concept and as a career. Theories of diplomatic and consular immunities and privileges are to be discussed as well.","3","https://www.state.gov/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/2018-DipConImm_v5_Web.pdf","POL 201"),
                 Course("Political Theory","POL 307","This course is divided into two basis sections. The first deals with the political values such as liberty, justice, equality, democracy, and power. The other section studies authority as a phenomenon. It includes a number of issues: Essence and content of authority, state functions and its theories, political behaviour, political obligations, as well as elite theory.","3","https://archive.mu.ac.in/myweb_test/M.A.(Part%20-%20I)%20Political%20Science%20Paper%20-%20I%20-%20Political%20Theory%20(Eng)%20-%20Rev.pdf","POL 201"),
                 Course("Egyptian Political Systems","POL 401","Developments in the Egyptian government and politics during the 20th century is the core of this course: constitutions, political life, parliaments, the three main powers: the Legislative, Executive, and Judicial, before and after the 1952 Revolution.","4","https://carnegieendowment.org/files/CP305_Dunne_and_Hamzawy_Parties_Final_Web.pdf","POL 302"),
                 Course("Comparative Political Systems","POL 402","This course deals with some examples of contemporary political systems. It is divided into two 'main parts: The first studies the developed political systems such as the U.S.A., the U.K., some nations in Asia and Africa such as China, India, and Nigeria.","4","https://gavsispanel.gelisim.edu.tr/Document/ycilliler/20190218092030868_829a7f14-9e76-4f4f-815d-b3f6f81288a9.pdf","POL 302"),
                 Course("Political Development","POL 403","Definition of political development is the starting point in this course. The following points include: Japanese, agents of development, crisis of development, and clash of civilizations. ","4","https://faculty.georgetown.edu/brumberg/govt778.pdf","POL 302"),
                 Course("Foreign Policies of Major Powers","POL 404","This course is designed to such countries in order to acquire power, influence and hegemony. A special attention is to be given to the policies of such powers towards the Arab World and the Middle East as well.","4","https://www.press.umich.edu/pdf/0472112872-ch2.pdf","POL 305"),
                 Course("Political Problems in the Arab World","POL 405","The focus of this course is the analysis of a number of the most important problems in the Arab region such as: Development, democracy, and human rights.","4","https://core.ac.uk/download/pdf/19578257.pdf","POL 305"),
                 Course("Contemporary Issues in World Politics","POL 406","This course deals with a number of the most important contemporary issues in the global arena. International crisis: theory and examples, globalization, new world order, and human rights are to be examined.","4","https://archive.mu.ac.in/myweb_test/TYBA%20study%20material/T.Y.B.A.%20Politics%20Paper%20-%20VI%20-Major%20issues%20in%20Contemporary%20Politics%20-%20Eng.pdf","POL 305"),
                 Course("Regional Organizations","POL 407","Topics included in this course are: theory of regionalism, relation between regional security and stability. Three regional organizations are thoroughly discussed, namely: the League of Arab States, the former Organization of African Unity (OAU), and the Organization of Islamic Conference regional arrangements such as OAS, ASEAN, APEC, and SARC.","4","https://reliefweb.int/sites/reliefweb.int/files/resources/1095455460.pdf","POL 304"),
                 Course("Egyptian Foreign Policy","POL 408","This Course deals with two major parts: First, the essential factors, geo strategic, which formulate the Egyptian political behaviour in the foreign science, such as the geographical location, population , armed forces and leadership. The other part concentrates on the circles of the Egyptian foreign policy: Arab, African, Islamic, and developing countries. Egyptian foreign policy towards the major powers: the USA, the UK.","4","https://eprints.ucm.es/id/eprint/47417/1/T39878.pdf","POL 305"))))

